### Political Footprint  

The **Sutherland‑Leveson‑Gower**s were not content to sit on their estates and look pretty.  Several family members held seats in the **House of Commons** before moving—inevitably—to the **House of Lords**.  Notably, **Francis Leveson‑Gower, 1st Earl of Gower** served as **Lord President of the Council** under **William Pitt the Younger**, while **Granville Leveson‑Gower, 2nd Earl of Gower** became **Foreign Secretary**.  Their political résumés read like a *who’s who* of 19th‑century British governance, complete with scandal‑prone affairs and a penchant for *grandiloquent speeches* that would make any modern politician blush.  

